    {
      "href": "/misscerrone/list/iranian-new-wave/",
      "user": "misscerrone",
      "slug": "iranian-new-wave",
      "title": "Iranian New Wave",
      "desc": "For my film students, a list of films to investigate if you are interested in this particular film movement. \n\n\"A film movement signifies a wave of cinematic works usually, following a particular trend in cinema, shaped by and reflecting the time, people, culture, and political events of the location from which it emerged. These cinematic works frequently draw inspiration from cultural roots, often influenced by events of national tragedy, popular culture, or social issues.\" (https://cinemawavesblog.com/)\n\nThe Iranian New Wave film movement emerged emerged in the late 1960s and continued through the 1970s. It is exploration of philosophical ideas, critiques of society, poetic disposition and experimentation. Other features of the movement are the use of non-professional actors, minimalistic settings, a focus… more",
